<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-DCFC99BC-56F8-492A-8522-777E09A86ECF" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-DCFC99BC-56F8-492A-8522-777E09A86ECF" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">01 The function of Curing</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The curing function takes care of the curing (pre, post and pin curing lamp ) of the UV gel ink on the media.
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="FIG_BF25F07CD6ED47A3806A8482DCEA921D"><title class="- topic/title ">Curing system (marked yellow)</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-522089B6-9654-4E1A-81BB-BCD3FE7C39CF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-522089B6-9654-4E1A-81BB-BCD3FE7C39CF-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="SECTION_E2C78FDC4E88474AAE461173D7F15EFA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The components of curing</title><ul id="UL_5442E400C31E4E73AEF039174FF849E5" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_FFAD08E7C045443FB765C34A0A911CC5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage. 
</p></li><li id="LI_04F7878390ED4455939ED4096DE1BFF6" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The linear guide rail. 
</p></li><li id="LI_8491DEE82E2B48CF8EC246EB310EA6A5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing lamps (pre curing and post and pin curing lamp). 
</p></li><li id="LI_81B7DE7AAA494861BC3B818541A7A19F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage crash sensors. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="01FUNC002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C81032B-89AA-4C1B-AD5D-045C3DC3F689.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 01 The process of the Lamp control PBA 01PBA03?>01 The process of the Lamp control PBA ( 01PBA03 ;)</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-E397C653-FAE4-4C40-8B73-DAE92481A365" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The gloss print mode &amp; the curing process</title><p class="- topic/p ">Overview curing process: 
</p><fig id="GUID-4C026175-3F84-417D-8733-D8A9B78EB41A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E1147A0E-F0C6-4690-98B3-477C28F097BD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E1147A0E-F0C6-4690-98B3-477C28F097BD-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-F5BA83DE-4787-4735-8B61-453C4489B457" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The UV gel ink is jetted, by the printheads, onto the media. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink droplets are on the media. The ink is not yet cured. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink droplets merge and become an even layer (film) on the media. The ink is not yet cured. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing of the ink is carried out with 2 UV LED lamps: the Pre curing lamp and Post and Pin curing lamp. The ink is united with the media. The ink type and the even layer of the ink, result in a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">gloss</b> view of the image. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-0A33A244-A4CA-4A97-8051-2AECC6AB5288" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The matte print mode &amp; the curing process</title><p class="- topic/p ">Overview curing process: 
</p><fig id="GUID-C10B64D6-5541-4C47-A959-BDBC86237454" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7807811F-E9C3-4814-9461-8C6B22F95BEE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7807811F-E9C3-4814-9461-8C6B22F95BEE-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-9958B401-2386-432F-AD45-118712D74AE8" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The UV gel ink is jetted, by the printheads, onto the media. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink droplets are on the media and immediately exposed with a low amount of UV light. The UV light cures only the top layer of the ink droplets. The UV light of the Post and Pin curing lamp (2 of the 5 segments) is reflected by 2 curved mirrors onto the media beside the printhead carriage. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink droplets merge a little bit (due to the cured top layer) and become an uneven top layer on the media. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing of the ink is carried out with 2 UV LED lamps: the Pre curing lamp and Post curing lamp. The ink is united with the media. The ink type and the uneven layer of the ink, result in a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">matte</b> view of the image. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_BE938E20C6C242DCB43B17BAA997C773" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The curing carriage </title><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage is used to move the 2 curing lamps over the media in order to cure the ink. The curing carriage moves along the linear guide rail in Y-direction. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> For correct curing the curing carriage moves at a fixed distance above the media. 
</p><fig id="FIG_0B81AC1515CA4F06A18507CCE1B42ADE" class="- topic/fig "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage with the components: 
</p></desc><image href="GUID-10CD6CEF-80E2-4597-B69A-AE68444504F8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-10CD6CEF-80E2-4597-B69A-AE68444504F8-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-5B2FAFDA-6322-4717-9E30-6E1FF41D7B4C" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Component 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01B5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage ruler sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_RUL_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01B6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage crash left sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CRASH_LEFT_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01B7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage crash right sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CRASH_RIGHT_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01PBA01 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">01PBA02 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pin Post Cure lamp PBA (UV LED lamp 75/50)</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA02 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">POST_PIN_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-22F0B060-2B2B-49D7-8AD2-708A923E5B66" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Lubrication</title><p class="- topic/p ">The lubrication of the curing carriage on the linear guide rail is done with 2 x 2 guidance cleaners. The felt is filled with oil. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Lifetime: the curing carriage guidance cleaners last either 1 year or 4600km travel of curing carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> A warning will be presented on the operator panel, when 95% of the age is reached (347 days or 4370km). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The replacement of the curing guidance cleaners is a key operator action. See<xref keyref="01DISA010" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-544AFD34-4B1B-44CE-AB6D-ABE84AE46EB6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 01 Replace the lubricators (technician)?>01 Replace the lubricators (technician)</xref> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The linear guide rail</title><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage is transported along a linear guide rail (1) from the left to the right hand side (Y-direction) and back, by 2 drive belts and motor. 
</p><fig id="GUID-42298EB1-FFA7-48D1-850B-FFE5478F0DF7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CF546B02-F20D-4830-A205-614AEC4B96F6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CF546B02-F20D-4830-A205-614AEC4B96F6-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The curing carriage is connected to a drive belt that is driven by the curing carriage motor (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_MO</compsignal></comp>). The motor speed is controlled using the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage motor encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_MO_ENC</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The cooling of the motor is done with an additional fan: <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage motor fan</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01M2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_MO_FAN</compsignal></comp>. The fan is located beside the motor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">There are 2 sensors that check the position of the curing carriage: 
</p><ul id="UL_43DCBBD8920943CCA4B63866CBCED27C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_AE20F53AA9284DA7B232FB100A1BC618" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">When the curing carriage is in its home position this is detected by <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage home sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_HOME_SE</compsignal></comp>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_188F8C4CDDC7413CBEAAADA54D001B7A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage ruler sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CAR_RUL_SE</compsignal></comp> is used as an indication of the current speed, direction and position of the curing carriage. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The curing lamps</title><p class="- topic/p ">There are 2 UV curing lamps mounted inside the curing carriage: 
</p><ul id="UL_98133C9BDB6A4A12A25B27A32AA33200" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_3065913D817745968D13661F8FA3F5F3" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This lamp has a wavelength of 405 nano meters and a power of approximately 140 Watts. 
</p></li><li id="LI_76FE5471ABB141459DEC0BD09A6A5DDD" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pin Post Cure lamp PBA (UV LED lamp 75/50)</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA02 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">POST_PIN_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This lamp has a wavelength of 385 nano meters and a power of approximately 80 Watts. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">The lamps have each a different operating area above the media on the platen (print surface). 
</p><fig id="FIG_5562179DD32B457BB580A10A819FC04E" class="- topic/fig "/><ul id="UL_F09E28A617F44B76BF330796DBFC3E1C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_4C31050D0A68460A8CE17DFBF19DF385" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The pre-curing lamp has an operating range of <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="mathsymbols">± </ph>200 mm. 
</p><fig id="GUID-5AEBD21D-2A2F-4EDF-9092-3B613FCC5A30" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5FE71B95-8062-4315-9252-666C7C2AFA02-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5FE71B95-8062-4315-9252-666C7C2AFA02-low.png"/></fig></li><li id="LI_A7E57219644442B39655FC6FD2749DBF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The post and pin curing lamp is mounted directly beside the pre-curing lamp. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Three of the 5 segments are used for post curing. The UV light is directly guided onto the media on the platen. This lamp has an operating range of <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="mathsymbols">± </ph>60 mm. 
</p><fig id="GUID-FCBEC1B2-30D8-410B-847B-7790A34B612F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AAE25CB3-9164-4365-A19D-5D8EDAFBCACA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AAE25CB3-9164-4365-A19D-5D8EDAFBCACA-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Two of the 5 segments can be used for the matte print modes. The light of the Post and Pin cure lamp is guided via 2 curved mirrors (top and bottom) to the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Via mirror on the printhead carriage the UV light is guided onto the print area beside the printhead carriage. Depending on the direction movement of the printhead carriage the mirror on the left or right hand side of the printhead carriage is used. The curing and printhead carriage move in synchrony. The top layer of the jetted ink on the media is instantly cured. The end result after pre and post curing is a matte layer of the ink. This curing has an operating range of 100 mm. 
</p><fig id="GUID-585640D7-2C78-4C95-B2F8-B28AD1529FFD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E82F032F-9EA4-4A0D-B8BB-CBE782D2C16F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E82F032F-9EA4-4A0D-B8BB-CBE782D2C16F-low.png"/></fig></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">The lamps can be used at various UV light intensities. The intensity is controlled via <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. The intensity largely depends on the amount of ink used and on the media type used. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-01DFA857-6429-4AC0-8066-468C4A389C67" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Cooling</title><p class="- topic/p ">The UV lamps need cooling otherwise they get too hot. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each lamp has 2 hose connections that are connected to the cooling system of the chiller unit. The cooling liquid of the chiller unit prevents overheating of the 2 lamps. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_58E9CF9940334A9BA99AB3B398327A46" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The curing carriage crash sensors</title><p class="- topic/p ">If the curing carriage crashes in to the media, the carriage unit must be stopped immediately and the curing lamps must be switched off. This will prevent damage to media and curing unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Media crashes are detected by <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage crash left sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CRASH_LEFT_SE</compsignal></comp> or <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Curing carriage crash right sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CUR_CRASH_RIGHT_SE</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><fig id="FIG_C93317B41AA64A9981BB5645365B8212" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8A9ADD03-556E-4C0A-B98E-E71F4A8A1210-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8A9ADD03-556E-4C0A-B98E-E71F4A8A1210-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At both left and right hand side there is a crash sensor. The sensors will be operated if the curing carriage is about to touch the media. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B6F5A54C-52D7-45D2-9AE2-815392CF0F57.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>